<Link id="l02095" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2095"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02096" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2096"><Highlight kind="comment">/// While solving the dataflow for a function, we don&#39;t compute a result for</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02097" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2097"><Highlight kind="comment">/// operations with an undef operand, to allow undef to be lowered to a</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02098" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2098"><Highlight kind="comment">/// constant later. For example, constant folding of &quot;zext i8 undef to i16&quot;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02099" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2099"><Highlight kind="comment">/// would result in &quot;i16 0&quot;, and if undef is later lowered to &quot;i8 1&quot;, then the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02100" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2100"><Highlight kind="comment">/// zext result would become &quot;i16 1&quot; and would result into an overdefined</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02101" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2101"><Highlight kind="comment">/// lattice value once merged with the previous result. Not computing the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02102" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2102"><Highlight kind="comment">/// result of the zext (treating undef the same as unknown) allows us to handle</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02103" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2103"><Highlight kind="comment">/// a later undef-&gt;constant lowering more optimally.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02104" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2104"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02105" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2105"><Highlight kind="comment">/// However, if the operand remains undef when the solver returns, we do need</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02106" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2106"><Highlight kind="comment">/// to assign some result to the instruction (otherwise we would treat it as</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02107" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2107"><Highlight kind="comment">/// unreachable). For simplicity, we mark any instructions that are still</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02108" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2108"><Highlight kind="comment">/// unknown as overdefined.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02109" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2109" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sccpinstvisitor/#a23d5e15d0e68537d608cc8ee21035f3d"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">bool</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sccpinstvisitor/#a23d5e15d0e68537d608cc8ee21035f3d">SCCPInstVisitor::resolvedUndefsIn</a>(<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/function">Function</a> &amp;<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/support/md5-cpp/#a96d73bbd7af15cb1fc38c3f4a3bd82e9">F</a>) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02110" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2110"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">bool</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> MadeChange = </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">false</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">;</Highlight></CodeLine>
